If You Just Bought a New Apple Device, You Get Free Apple TV+

   Nick Douglas
   Yesterday 3:15pm
   Filed to:TV

   If you bought a new iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, Apple TV, or Mac after
   September 10 this year, then you can get a free year of Apple TV+
   (normally $5/month). The streaming service launches November 1, after
   which you’ll have three months to activate your free year in the Apple
   TV app. (If you buy a new device after November 1, you’ll have three
   months from the purchase date to activate.)

   TV+ launches with a slate of original shows and films, including The
   Morning Show, which is like ... daytime Newsroom? See more trailers on
   Apple’s site.

   Advertisement

   After your free year, TV+ will auto-renew for a month at $5. To cancel
   without missing some of your free subscription, set a calendar alert
   for a couple of days before your free year runs out, and include a link
   to the cancellation page.

   If you already intended to pay for the streaming service, then consider
   this a $60 discount on a device purchase. On the $150 Apple TV, that’s
   actually a consideration. But don’t use this to justify a new iPhone.

   Details for the deal are available on the Apple TV+ page and in this
   PDF.

   Advertisement

